title: Visiting Professor Diljit Singh
description: Dr. Diljit Singh, visiting professor from the University of Malaya, has been conducting regular visists to the SLIS since 2016. He has provided valuable wisdom along the lines of LIS research, journal publications, and curriculum development. He has overseen faculty and student research via numberous SLIS Student Research Fora, Qualatative Research Seminars and Workshops, and the refocusing of the research agenda of the faculty and school as whole. Dr. Diljit Singh also served as the SLIS Recognition Speaker for graduating batch iNVICTUS for 2018.
subject: Diljit Singh; visiting professor
rights: Educational use includes non-commercial use of text and images in materials for teaching and research purposes. Digital reproduction rights granted by the UP SLIS.

title: Visiting Professor Mona Jimenez
description: Prof. Mona Jimenez, visisting professor from New York University, is a leading advocate of the CAAW or Community Archiving Workshops. She helped SLIS start the Community Archiving Workshops in 2017. She delivered her Visiting Professor Lecture on "Community Archiving: Theories and Initatives." on 29 March 2018 at the UP Main Library. During her visit she handled LIS 217 classes, oversaw Community Archiving Initatives involving LIS students, engaged in research and coauthored an article with SLIS faculty, served as consultant for UP SLIS and the UP Main Library in developing preservation laboratories, and prsented at the 21st SEAPAVAA Conference together with MLIS students.
subject: Mona Jimenez; visiting professor
rights: Educational use includes non-commercial use of text and images in materials for teaching and research purposes. Digital reproduction rights granted by the UP SLIS.

title: Visiting Professor Dr. Thomas Nesmith
description: Dr. Thomas Nesmith, Senior Scholar, Archival Studies, Uniersity of Manitoba, is known for his explications on the concept of Societal Provenance. During his visit he handled LIS 170 and 171 classes, talked about the role of Archives as LIbraries' Partners in Societal Transformation at the plenary session of the 2018 PLAI Congress, served as consultant for the development of the Archives and Doctoral degress of the SLIS, and delivered a public lecture entitled: "Archives, Libraries, and the Reflections of the Yuval Noah Harari on "The New Human Agend" to close out the LIS month.
